    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-03-23T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="265"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d265">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Colonel <persName type="from">J. Hart Caughey</persName> to
                        Lieutenant General <persName type="to">Alvan C. Gillem, Jr.</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Yenan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-03-23">23 March
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Chou will return Sunday if Chang agrees to signing of short 3 paragraphs
                        agreement<note n="39" xml:id="d265fn1">See draft prepared by General Chou
                        En-lai, March 16, <ref target="#pg_564">p. 564</ref>.</note> with following
                    change:</p>
                <p>Insert words “and fair” in front of word “Readjustments” in paragraph 3 and
                    inclusion in minutes of statement in bottom of page.</p>
                <p>Chou favors this and I believe Chang will agree. Please contact Chang so you can
                    let me know urgent. Chou’s return depends upon your reply. Chou redrafted 7
                    point agreement<note n="39" xml:id="d265fn2">See draft prepared by General Chou
                        En-lai, March 16, <ref target="#pg_564">p. 564</ref>.</note> as follows: <list>
                        <item>First paragraph same as first paragraph of short agreement.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 2, no change.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 3, insert “and fair” before “Readjustments”.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 4, no change.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 5, no change.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 6, delete.</item>
                        <item>Paragraph 7, delete, and then enter it as a matter of record.</item>
                    </list>
                </p>
                <p>This is Chou’s alternative and may be used as basis for further discussion.
                    Another less urgent message follows.<note n="40" xml:id="d265fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Infra</hi>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caughey</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
